  "prompt": "Why is Milan, Italy a fashion capital?",
  "response": "Milan has become a global fashion capital for several reasons:\n\n1. Historical significance\n- Long tradition of textile and clothing manufacturing\n- Influential design houses and fashion brands originated here\n- Home to many prestigious fashion companies like Prada, Versace, and Armani\n\n2. Fashion infrastructure\n- Hosts Milan Fashion Week twice annually\n- Major international fashion trade shows and exhibitions\n- Numerous prestigious fashion schools and design institutes\n\n3. Industrial expertise\n- Strong textile and manufacturing industries\n- Advanced craftsmanship and tailoring techniques\n- High-quality production standards\n\n4. Cultural reputation\n- Italians are known for style and aesthetic appreciation\n- Strong emphasis on design and elegance\n- Global recognition for sophisticated fashion sense\n\n5. Economic importance\n- Fashion and luxury goods are significant contributors to the city's economy\n- Many international fashion brands have headquarters or major operations in Milan\n- Attracts global fashion professionals and designers\n\n6. Creative ecosystem\n- Dense network of designers, manufacturers, and fashion professionals\n- Supportive environment for fashion innovation\n- Continuous evolution of design and style\n\nThese factors have collectively established Milan as one of the world's most important fashion centers, alongside Paris, New York, and London.",
